.Dl RESCALE
.Pp
Allows you to change the image\(aqs size,
rescaling it accordingly. Enter new size
and press RESIZE to confirm.
.Pp
.
When \(aqLock proportions\(aq is checked and you
change one dimension, the other one is
automatically adjusted to preserve the
proportions of the original image.
.Pp
You can use the dropdown button to choose
between three ways to enter the dimensions:
.Pp
In \(aqPixels\(aq mode, the column \(aqold\(aq shows
the original dimensions, and you can set
the new size in pixels.
.Pp
In \(aqPercent\(aq mode, you set a percentage
compared to the original image.
.Pp
In \(aqRatio\(aq mode, you can set 2 numbers for
each dimension, and the resizing factor will
be of \(aqnew\(aq÷\(aqold\(aq. For example you can use
1:3 to divide the image by three, 2:1 to
double it, and any fraction like 15:16.
.Pp
Be careful that moving from one mode to the
next can lose precision, if the selected
dimensions cannot be represented exactly in
the new mode.
.Pp
